gn=left class=m><span class=title> how does one powerlevel a cleric</span><hr size=1> All this talk about PLing characters. I'm assuming that in order for the exp to level you would need to do over half the damage and make the kill. Since clerics dont really melee, or shouldnt melee, over level 14 how would this get accomplished? <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udollie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dollie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/10/01 2:12:13 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: how does one powerlevel a cleric</span><hr size=1> Get a damage shield, nuke once, heal yourself after mob is dead =p but this wont work very long...<br>
<br>
You can always ask someone to kill the mob till it runs, ask a chanter to mez or use atone if over level 34 then finish the mob with a nuke.<br>
<br>
Anyway if you get powerleveled, chances are that your casting skills will be soooooo bad you will have to take the time you saved leveling working on your skills....<br>
<br>
Hard to powerlevel a caster...<br>
<br>
Just a thought <p><b><font face = "garamond" color="#E1C168">Celest<br>
High Nurse of the 60th bandaid<br>
Fallen Legacy<br>
</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udollie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dollie</A> at: 12/10/01 2:13:12 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uuilarblakheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Uilar Blakheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/10/01 3:09:59 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: how does one powerlevel a cleric</span><hr size=1> Powerleveling a cleric is not wise.  I powerlvld my cleric with quests.  Got him to lvl 6 in about an hour and a half.  Then when I tried to play him, I was not able to hit mobs often because my melee skills were lacking, and I was fizzling alot because my casting skills sucked.  <br>
<br>
Uilaar Darkheartt<br>
54 Vicar<br>
Silent Avengers <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usalamren.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Salamren</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.home.net/dober17/hobbes.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/10/01 4:24:04 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/dober17/hobbes.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: how does one powerlevel a cleric</span><hr size=1> Another thing to condider is defense. If you PL your cleric, and your defense skill is low you'll go down as fast as a robe class if you get agro, and if you are PLed that will probably happen quite a bit.<br>
<br>
