<img src="http://www.ee.ualberta.ca/~nancy/raisins.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udarwinianseafarer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Darwinian Seafarer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/10/01 5:08:18 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: how does one powerlevel a cleric</span><hr size=1> Find yourself a necro.<br>
<br>
Chanters work okay too...<br>
<br>
The damage shield thing is a good idea, never tried it, dunno how long/well it'd be effective though.<br>
<br>
I don't advise powerleveling a cleric. Cast your way through your levels, getting a spell skill up from 5 at level 30 would suck ass.<br>
<br>
See also; Divination; Unrest; Invis vs Undead<br>
<br>
Cast that sense the dead spell early folks..<br>
<br>
